# Microsoft Graph API (Outlook calendar)
# Docs: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/calendar
#
# Token: MS_GRAPH_TOKEN is short-lived (~1h). To refresh, see the `api-tests`
# skill — it walks sc_id → refresh_token → fresh access_token, either off-DB
# (read-only, prod-safe) or write-back (local only). MS sometimes rotates the
# refresh_token in the response; off-DB path discards it (safe — next sync
# picks it up).
#
# event.type values:
#   singleInstance   non-recurring event
#   seriesMaster     master of a recurring series; carries `recurrence`
#   occurrence       unmodified instance of a series
#   exception        modified instance (links back via seriesMasterId)
# Cancelled occurrences appear with isCancelled=true.
#
# Common params / headers:
#   $top                       page size, default 10, cap 1000
#   $select                    comma-separated allow-list (avoid huge payloads)
#   $orderby                   e.g. "lastModifiedDateTime desc"
#   $filter                    OData, e.g. "type eq 'seriesMaster'"
#   Prefer: outlook.timezone="UTC"        return all times in UTC (Pad expects this)
#   Prefer: outlook.body-content-type="text"   plain text body instead of HTML
#
# Useful jq slices:
#   calendars: jq '.value[] | {id, name, isDefaultCalendar, owner: .owner.address}'
#   events:    jq '.value[] | {id, subject, start, end, type, seriesMasterId, isCancelled}'

### List the user's calendars
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/calendars
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}

### Get the default calendar
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/calendar
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}

### List events in the default calendar
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/calendar/events?$top=50&$orderby=start/dateTime&$select=id,subject,start,end,recurrence,type,seriesMasterId,isCancelled
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}
Prefer: outlook.timezone="UTC"

### Calendar view (expanded recurring instances) for a date range
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/calendar/calendarView?startDateTime=2026-04-25T00:00:00Z&endDateTime=2026-05-25T00:00:00Z&$top=999&$select=id,subject,start,end,seriesMasterId,isCancelled,type
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}
Prefer: outlook.timezone="UTC"

### Get a single event by id
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/events/{{MS_EVENT_ID}}
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}

### Delta query (incremental sync). Use the @odata.deltaLink from a previous response.
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/{{MS_USER_ID}}/calendarView/delta?startDateTime=2026-04-25T00:00:00Z&endDateTime=2026-05-25T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}
Prefer: outlook.timezone="UTC"

### Subscribe to change notifications (webhook)
POST https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/subscriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{MS_GRAPH_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "changeType": "created,updated,deleted",
  "notificationUrl": "https://example.com/webhook",
  "resource": "/me/events",
  "expirationDateTime": "2026-05-25T00:00:00Z",
  "clientState": "secret-client-state"
}
